      "content": "While your love for your daughter is genuine, framing your presence as a \"problem\" or an unfair burden ignores the immense strength it takes for her to support you; many people find great peace in knowing they are needed by someone who has loved them selflessly. Please know that healing isn't just about your legs getting better immediately, but about allowing yourself to rest without the crushing guilt of feeling like a burden on those who care for you. If your physical abilities have declined this far, that is a reflection of your illness, not a reflection of your worth or the value you bring to your family's life.",
